name: Toddle Along
subtitle: walk baby walk
backText: "Don’t walk in front of me… I may not follow, Don’t walk behind me… I may not lead, Walk beside me… just be my friend "
author: Albert Camus

name: See No Evil
subtitle: shy kitty
backText: "If you are allergic to a thing, it is best not to put that thing in your mouth, particularly if the thing is cats."
author: Lemony Snicket, The Wide Window

name: Blown Away
subtitle: ride the wind
backText: No matter how the wind howls. The mountain cannot bow to it."
author: Walt Disney Co., Mulan

name: Tenuous Path
subtitle: road less traveled
backText: "Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail."
author: Ralph Waldo Emerson
